    "If G = (V, E) is a k-path graph, and Q ⊂ V is a k-clique containing at least one simplicial vertex, then for any vertex v / ∈ V, the augmented graphG ′ = (V ∪ {v}, E ∪ {{v, w} | w ∈ Q} also is a k-path graph.For k-trees, which are chordal graphs, the number of edges and the chromatic number are known ( [21], [9]).",
